<p>和监督学习区别</p>
<ul>
<li>Trial-and-error exploration</li>
<li>delayed reward<br>不会得到立刻的反馈</li>
<li>Time matters Sequential data</li>
<li>data之间是连续的<br>只有到最后游戏结束才有label，因此单个的action没有一个确切的label告诉你是否正确，存在奖励的延迟</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="Sequential-Decision-Making"><a href="#Sequential-Decision-Making" class="headerlink" title="Sequential Decision Making"></a>Sequential Decision Making</h2><p>Environment state and agent state</p>
<p><img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801093617789.png" alt="image-20210801093617789"></p>
<p><strong>Full observability</strong>： agent directly observes the environment state, formally as Markov decision process (MDP)<br>    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801094310027.png" alt="image-20210801094310027" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<p><strong>Partial observability</strong>： agent indirectly observes the environment, formally as partially observable Markov decision process (POMDP)</p>
<h2 id="Policy"><a href="#Policy" class="headerlink" title="Policy"></a>Policy</h2><p>根据观测的状态做出选择</p>
<ul>
<li><p>A policy is the agent’s behavior model</p>
</li>
<li><p>a map function from state/observation to action</p>
</li>
