<h2 id="Markov-Decision-Process-MDP"><a href="#Markov-Decision-Process-MDP" class="headerlink" title="Markov Decision Process (MDP)"></a>Markov Decision Process (MDP)</h2><p>Markov Reward Process with decisions</p>
<p><strong>Definition</strong> </p>
<ul>
<li>S is a finite set of states</li>
<li>A is a finite set of actions</li>
<li>$P^a$ is dynamics/transition model for each action<br>$P(s_{t+1} = s’|s_t = s ,a_t = a) $</li>
<li><em>R</em> is a reward function<br>$R(s_t = s,a_t = a) = E[r_t|s_t= s,a_t= a]$ </li>
<li>Discount factor <em>γ</em> <em>∈</em> [0<em>,</em> 1]</li>
</ul>
<p>MDP is a tuple: (S, A,P,R, γ)</p>
<h3 id="Policy-in-MDP"><a href="#Policy-in-MDP" class="headerlink" title="Policy in MDP"></a>Policy in MDP</h3><p>Policy specifies what action to take in each state<br>Give a state, specify a distribution over actions<br>Policy: $π(a|s) =P(a_t = a|s_t = s)$ </p>
<p>Policies are stationary (time-independent), </p>
<p>$A_t ∼ π(a|s) for \ any\  t&gt; 0$</p>
<p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801161022035.png" alt="image-20210801161022035" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<h3 id="Comparison-of-MP-MRP-and-MDP"><a href="#Comparison-of-MP-MRP-and-MDP" class="headerlink" title="Comparison of MP/MRP and MDP"></a>Comparison of MP/MRP and MDP</h3><p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801161039681.png" alt="image-20210801161039681" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<h3 id="Value-function-for-MDP"><a href="#Value-function-for-MDP" class="headerlink" title="Value function for MDP"></a>Value function for MDP</h3><p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801161420304.png" alt="image-20210801161420304" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<p><strong>Bellman方程</strong></p>
<p>$q_{\pi}(s,a) = \mathbb{E}_{\pi}(G_t|S_t=s, A_t=a) = \mathbb{E}_{\pi}(R_{t+1} + \gamma R_{t+2} + \gamma^2R_{t+3}+…|S_t=s,A_t=a)$</p>
<p>$\begin{align} v_{\pi}(s) &amp;= \mathbb{E}_{\pi}(R_{t+1} + \gamma R_{t+2} + \gamma^2R_{t+3}+…|S_t=s) \\ &amp;= \mathbb{E}_{\pi}(R_{t+1} + \gamma (R_{t+2} + \gamma R_{t+3}+…)|S_t=s) \\ &amp;= \mathbb{E}_{\pi}(R_{t+1} + \gamma G_{t+1} | S_t=s) \\ &amp;=  \mathbb{E}_{\pi}(R_{t+1} + \gamma v_{\pi}(S_{t+1}) | S_t=s) \end{align}$</p>
<p>也就是说，在t时刻的状态S_t和t+1时刻的状态S_{t+1}是满足递推关系的，即：</p>
<p>$v_{\pi}(s) = \mathbb{E}_{\pi}(R_{t+1} + \gamma v_{\pi}(S_{t+1}) | S_t=s)$</p>
<p>同样的方法，我们可以得到动作价值函数q_{\pi}(s,a)的贝尔曼方程：</p>
<p>$q_{\pi}(s,a) = \mathbb{E}_{\pi}(R_{t+1} + \gamma q_{\pi}(S_{t+1},A_{t+1}) | S_t=s, A_t=a)$</p>
<h3 id="Bellman-Expectation-Equation"><a href="#Bellman-Expectation-Equation" class="headerlink" title="Bellman Expectation Equation"></a>Bellman Expectation Equation</h3><p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801161628866.png" alt="image-20210801161628866" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<p>​      $v_{\pi}(s) = \sum\limits_{a \in A} \pi(a|s)q_{\pi}(s,a)$</p>
<p>状态价值函数是所有动作价值函数基于策略$\pi$的期望。通俗说就是某状态下所有状态动作价值乘以该动作出现的概率，最后求和，就得到了对应的状态价值。</p>
<p>$q_{\pi}(s,a) = R_s^a + \gamma \sum\limits_{s’ \in S}P_{ss’}^av_{\pi}(s’)$</p>
<p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801161727430.png" alt="image-20210801161727430" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<h3 id="Backup-Diagram"><a href="#Backup-Diagram" class="headerlink" title="Backup Diagram"></a>Backup Diagram</h3><p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801161957419.png" alt="image-20210801161957419" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801162006501.png" alt="image-20210801162006501" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<h3 id="Policy-Evaluation"><a href="#Policy-Evaluation" class="headerlink" title="Policy Evaluation"></a>Policy Evaluation</h3><p>Evaluate the value of state given a policy <em>π</em>: compute $v^π(s) $</p>
<p>Also called as (value) prediction</p>
<h3 id="Decision-Making-in-Markov-Decision-Process-MDP"><a href="#Decision-Making-in-Markov-Decision-Process-MDP" class="headerlink" title="Decision Making in Markov Decision Process (MDP)"></a>Decision Making in Markov Decision Process (MDP)</h3><p><strong>Prediction (evaluate a given policy)</strong>    </p>
<p>Input: MDP$ &lt; S,A,P,R, γ &gt; $and policy <em>π</em> or MRP $&lt; S,P^π,R^π, γ &gt;$ </p>
<p>Output: value function $v^π$ </p>
<p><strong>Control (search the optimal policy):</strong></p>
<p>Input: $MDP <S,A,P,R,γ>$</p>
<p>Output: optimal value function <em>v</em>$ ^∗$ and optimal policy $π^∗$ </p>
<p>Prediction and control in MDP can be solved by <strong>dynamic programming</strong></p>
<h3 id="Dynamic-Programming"><a href="#Dynamic-Programming" class="headerlink" title="Dynamic Programming"></a>Dynamic Programming</h3><p>Optimal substructure<br>Overlapping subproblems</p>
<p>Markov decision processes satisfy both properties</p>
<ul>
<li>Bellman equation gives recursive decomposition</li>
<li>Value function stores and reuses solutions</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="Policy-evaluation-on-MDP"><a href="#Policy-evaluation-on-MDP" class="headerlink" title="Policy evaluation on MDP"></a>Policy evaluation on MDP</h3><p><strong>Objective:</strong> Evaluate a given policy <em>π</em> for a MDP</p>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> the value function under policy $v^π$</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong> iteration on Bellman expectation backup</p>
<p><strong>Algorithm:</strong> Synchronous backup</p>
<p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801170204507.png" alt="image-20210801170204507" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<p><img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801170215355.png" alt="image-20210801170215355" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<p>Bellman expectation backup for a particular <strong>policy</strong></p>
<p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801170357916.png" alt="image-20210801170357916" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801170416568.png" alt="image-20210801170416568" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<h3 id="Optimal-Value-Function"><a href="#Optimal-Value-Function" class="headerlink" title="Optimal Value Function"></a>Optimal Value Function</h3><p><strong>optimal state-value function</strong> $v ^∗(s)$ is the maximum value function over all policies</p>
<p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801172609642.png" alt="image-20210801172609642" style="zoom:50%;" /><br><strong>optimal policy</strong></p>
<p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801172728339.png" alt="image-20210801172728339" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<p>There exists a unique optimal value function, but could be multiple optimal policies (two actions that have the same optimal value function)</p>
<p><strong>Finding Optimal Policy</strong><br>    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801172843291.png" alt="image-20210801172843291" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<p>There is always a deterministic optimal policy for any MDP</p>
<p>If we know $q^*(s, a)$, we immediately have the optimal policy</p>
<p>最优价值函数关系也很容易得到：<br>$q_{<em>}(s,a) = R_s^a + \gamma \sum\limits_{s’ \in S}P_{ss’}^av_{</em>}(s’)$</p>
<p>$v_{<em>}(s) = \max_a(R_s^a + \gamma \sum\limits_{s’ \in S}P_{ss’}^av_{</em>}(s’))$</p>
<p>$<br>q_{<em>}(s,a) = R_s^a + \gamma \sum\limits_{s’ \in S}P_{ss’}^a\max_{a’}q_{</em>}(s’,a’)$</p>
<h3 id="MDP-Control"><a href="#MDP-Control" class="headerlink" title="MDP Control"></a>MDP Control</h3><p>如何寻找最佳策略 得到最大价值函数</p>
<h4 id="Policy-iteration"><a href="#Policy-iteration" class="headerlink" title="Policy iteration"></a>Policy iteration</h4><p><strong>Evaluate</strong> the policy <em>π</em> (computing <em>v</em> given current <em>π</em>) 第一步是使用当前策略 π∗评估计算当前策略的最终状态价值 v∗</p>
<p><strong>Improve</strong> the policy by acting greedily with respect to $v^π$<br>根据状态价值 v∗根据一定的方法（比如贪婪法）更新策略 π∗</p>
<p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801193433409.png" alt="image-20210801193433409" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801193442853.png" alt="image-20210801193442853" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<p>Compute the state-action value of a policy <em>π</em>:</p>
<p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801193539751.png" alt="image-20210801193539751" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<p>Compute new policy$\ π_{i+1}$ for all <em>s</em> <em>∈ S</em> following</p>
<p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801193633305.png" alt="image-20210801193633305" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<p><strong>Monotonic Improvement in Policy</strong></p>
<p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801193834537.png" alt="image-20210801193834537" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801193943618.png" alt="image-20210801193943618" style="zoom: 50%;" /></p>
<h4 id="Bellman-Optimality-Equation"><a href="#Bellman-Optimality-Equation" class="headerlink" title="Bellman Optimality Equation"></a>Bellman Optimality Equation</h4><p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801194054261.png" alt="image-20210801194054261" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<h4 id="Value-iteration"><a href="#Value-iteration" class="headerlink" title="Value iteration"></a>Value iteration</h4><p>by turning the Bellman Optimality Equation as update rule</p>
<p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801194303716.png" alt="image-20210801194303716" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<p>Objective: fifind the optimal policy <em>π</em><br>Solution: iteration on the Bellman optimality backup<br>    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801194354867.png" alt="image-20210801194354867" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<h5 id="Difference-between-Policy-Iteration-and-Value-Iteration"><a href="#Difference-between-Policy-Iteration-and-Value-Iteration" class="headerlink" title="Difference between Policy Iteration and Value Iteration"></a>Difference between Policy Iteration and Value Iteration</h5><ul>
<li><p>Policy iteration includes: <strong>policy evaluation</strong> + <strong>policy improvement</strong>, and the two are repeated iteratively until policy converges.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Value iteration includes: <strong>fifinding optimal value function</strong> + <strong>one</strong></p>
<p><strong>policy extraction</strong>. There is no repeat of the two because once the value function is optimal, then the policy out of it should also be optimal (i.e. converged).</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p>  <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210801195527498.png" alt="image-20210801195527498"></p>
<h2 id="Review"><a href="#Review" class="headerlink" title="Review"></a>Review</h2><p>  MDP is known<br>  Both <strong><em>R</em></strong> and <strong><em>P</em></strong> are exposed to the agent</p>
<p>  Therefore,  policy iteration and value iteration</p>
<p>  <strong>Policy iteration</strong>: Given a <strong>known</strong> MDP, compute the optimal policy and the optimal value function</p>
<p>  <strong>Policy evaluation:</strong> iteration on the Bellman expectation backup</p>
<p>  ​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210802103147323.png" alt="image-20210802103147323"></p>
<p>  <strong>Policy improvement:</strong> <strong>greedy</strong> on action-value function <em>q</em></p>
<p>  ​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210802103505385.png" alt="image-20210802103505385" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<p>​    <strong>Value iteration:</strong> Given a <strong>known</strong> MDP, compute the optimal value function    </p>
<p>​    Iteration on the Bellman optimality backup<br>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210802103739155.png" alt="image-20210802103739155"></p>
<p>​    To retrieve the optimal policy after the value iteration:</p>
<p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210802103747824.png" alt="image-20210802103747824" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<p>​    <img src="https://pig-1307013046.cos.ap-nanjing.myqcloud.com/PigCo/image-20210802103821928.png" alt="image-20210802103821928" style="zoom:50%;" /></p>
<p>​    </p>
]]></content>
